Package: simulateDCE
Title: Simulate Data for Discrete Choice Experiments
Version: 0.3.1
Authors@R: person(given = "Julian", family = "Sagebiel", email =
        "julian.sagebiel@idiv.de", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment =
        c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0253-6875"))
Description: Supports simulating choice experiment data for given
        designs. It helps to quickly test different designs against
        each other and compare the performance of new models. The goal
        of 'simulateDCE' is to make it easy to simulate choice
        experiment datasets using designs from 'NGENE', 'idefix' or
        'spdesign'. You have to store the design file(s) in a
        sub-directory and need to specify certain parameters and the
        utility functions for the data generating process. For more
        details on choice experiments see Mariel et al. (2021)
        <doi:10.1007/978-3-030-62669-3>.
